  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nI'm currently trying to sync an Ethereum mainnet full node on an ARM64 single board with Geth. While the block syncing went well, the number of peers seems to be limited to 16 peers max when I'm using the flag `--maxpeers 50`. I have tested two different locations with high-speed Internet connections and no obvious firewall limitations and with two different versions (geth-1.9.0-stable and geth-1.8.7-stable) but the problem seems to be the same.\r\n\r\nYou can see below some metrics taken while syncing, the last two showing `admin.peers.length`\r\n\r\n**Block sync (geth-1.9.0)**\r\n![](https://i.imgur.com/Y01O8Zy.png)\r\n\r\n**State sync (geth-1.9.0)**\r\n![](https://i.imgur.com/dIKHJUd.png)\r\n\r\n**Peers (geth-1.9.0)**\r\n![](https://i.imgur.com/7Q7CWX3.png)\r\n\r\n**Peers (geth-1.8.7) - only 10 hours**\r\n![](https://i.imgur.com/4hpwcOo.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### System information\r\n\r\n**Geth options:** `geth --syncmode fast --cache 2048 --maxpeers 50 --datadir /mnt/ssd/ethereum`\r\n**Geth version:** 1.9.0-stable and 1.8.7-stable\r\n**Machine:** [NanoPi-M4](http://wiki.friendlyarm.com/wiki/index.php/NanoPi_M4) (arm64 6 cores, 4GB RAM, USB 3.0)\r\n**Disk:** SSD SanDisk Plus 256GB\r\n**OS:** [ARMBian](https://www.armbian.com/) (Debian Stretch)\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nShould reach more peers (max 50)\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nNumber of peers oscillating between 15-16 peers.\r\n\r\n### Backtrace\r\n\r\nLogs of the last attempt using geth-1.8.7-stable during 10 hours.\r\n\r\nhttps://gist.githubusercontent.com/gjeanmart/21c83a5b7d1e33925861577c12d67b48/raw/267e17b9b91fab4b666401a0e08f7c831fe90934/gistfile1.txt\r\n",
